At the present time, Indonesia is the focus of western and American business.  There is a large population of now mostly literate and semi-skilled workers, but still with relatively low salaries, so a lot of American business is going there to do the kind of factory work that used to be done in Hong Kong, South Korea, Taiwan, Thailand and Malaysia.  Those English-speaking Indonesians are an important part of the present Indonesian economic climate.


1975: Back to a Third Assignment in DepState's Cultural Bureau;
Then, in 1978, to Burma as Director of American Cultural Center, Rangoon
